<br>
In the interest of explaination, until Luclin came out the only thing paladins had going for us in the high end game where a couple class only spells that were useful (Celestial Cleansing and Divine Strength), and our tanking abilities in xp groups.  Our damage was hamstrung by a bugged combat engine, and nearly all of our buffs are overwritten by clerics.  We didn't have a definitive roll on end game encounters and couldn't step in to tank an ubermob for even a couple of seconds without some form of mitigation/avoidance discipline like all the other melee types, except SKs, have.  So, yes there was a good bit of class envy about that.  One of our usual rolls, i.e. back up tanking, wasn't available to us due to a bugged defensive engine that didn't let the &quot;defensive&quot; hybrids do jack squat defensively on uber mobs.  The reason warriors are preferred for ToV and higher mobs is Defensive disc.  Even then, most people on this board realized that we couldn't get even a watered down version of it without trivializing warriors.  Most of us would like to be able to step in when the do-do hits the revolving blades like rangers or bards or monk or rogues could when absolutely necessary.  But we didn't want to replace warriors in their only roll.<br>
<br>
What we did as a community, however, was come up with a unique roll - AE Healer.  Led by Kruegen of FoH, we were able to convince them that such an ability would give us a nice roll on raids.  Guess what?  We got it, it's call Healing Wave of Prexus ... perhaps you've heard of it? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->     It's such a nice roll that druids want a piece of our action.  Go figure them being envious of us? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Most of us would still like to see our disciplines mean something.  And most would like something similiar to the ranger avoidance one.  Most realize that we can't get defensive because that's the one roll that warriors have.  Thus, seeing VI's reluctance to allow &quot;defensive&quot; hybrids from fulfilling their defensive roll, we will probably continue to offer alternative solutions.<br>
<br>
I would love to be able to tank better.  I'm the MA/puller for my guild.  But I do NOT want to be a warrior.  With the AA skills I can make myself a better MA for my guild ... if I want to.  Or I can increase my damage.  Or I can improve my casting abilities.  Whatever, it's my choice now ... not Verants entirely.<br>
<br>
You want to tank ubermobs in Ssra?  Go for it!  I don't <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   I'd much prefer to get Slay Undead and make up for the damage you loose when you hit /disc defensive.  With Luclin we are finally PALADINS again ... something we haven't been since the release of RoK.  Not a part-warrior/part-Cleric gimp.  PALADINS!  And I'm happy about it <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=69612">Baron Taallyn Nifesblade</a><BR>
